snippet: The move by the newly elected Parliament set off a struggle for control of the country’s wealth and vast oil reserves.
abstract: Libya's newly elected Parliament votes to fire its central bank chairman Sadel Omar el-Kaber, setting off struggle for control of country's vast oil reserves.
lead_paragraph: The move by the newly elected Parliament set off a struggle for control of the country’s wealth and vast oil reserves.

headline.main: Libyan Parliament Fires Central Bank Chairman
